            <title>[THRIFT-5134] Fix memory leak when the handler method return FALSE</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-5134</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The memory leak was triggered on calling the handler method with return&lt;br/&gt;
FALSE. Because the return_value has been malloced when get property from&lt;br/&gt;
the result_struct. The return_value need to be freed as necessary.&lt;/p&gt;

